President Donald Trump issued a proclamation recognizing National Charter Schools Week and emphasizing the important contributions that public charter schools make to American families. He highlights that charter schools provide high-quality education options that meet the needs of students and empower families to choose the right educational fit for their children. The proclamation also mentions that charter schools have been successful in serving low-income students, minority students, and students learning English. President Trump expresses his commitment to reducing the federal footprint in education and empowering families, state, and local policymakers, and educators to adapt to student needs. He calls for increased funding for charter schools and emphasizes that all children deserve access to education that enriches their minds. The proclamation concludes by proclaiming May 12 through May 18, 2019, as National Charter Schools Week and calling on states and communities to support high-quality charter schools as an important school choice option.